title: tentacle_clothes
body:
Quite simply, tentacles that originate from clothing. There are a number of permutations. They may appear to be normal clothes with the tentacles completely or mostly concealed, or the tentacles could be freely sprouting from the clothing. The the clothing itself may be made of tentacles. The tentacles may or may not be a part of/under control of the wearer; if so, the tags [[dark persona]] and [[corruption]] are often associated.

Often, the subject clothing is a [[swimsuit]] or [[bodysuit]].

For tagging purposes, this tag encompass not just the "tentacle clothing" (触手服) pixiv tag, but also "tentacle suit" (触手スーツ) and "tentacle armor" (触手鎧).

title: rush_(object)
body:
Gatling 033 (ガトリング033, Gatoringu 033), also known by the codenames Rush (ラッシュ, Rasshu) and Henrietta (アンリエッタ, Anrietta), is a Second Generation Object of the Information Alliance's Sky Dog(br) 3rd C.E.B, piloted by the Elite commonly referred to as "Oh ho ho".

The Gatling 033 is made up of a spherical main body with a cross-shaped float and treads located directly below that. The floats extend to the front, back, left, and right. The two to the left and the right each have a rapid fire beam cannon Gatling gun installed on the top of the end.

It has over 100 cannons, both large and small, but it does not have all that many on the side. It has almost 20 smaller cannons on each side. This is likely to give priority to the main cannons.

The cockpit is a sphere of about 2 meters across with a giant monitor attached to the front. A large number of keyboards are lined up on three stepped levels. The third step spreads out in a U-shape around the edge of the cockpit. In the space not taken up by keyboards, an inscription reads “Manual Interface ‘JULIET’.

title: baby_magnum
body:
Baby Magnum (ベイビーマグナム, Beibīmagunamu) is a First Generation Composite Multi-Role Object of the Legitimacy Kingdom's 37th Mobile Maintenance Battalion, piloted by Milinda Brantini.

Baby Magnum is over 50m tall with a spherical main body. The cockpit is located in the center of the main body and is itself a sphere about 2m in diameter, with monitors curved around the inside of the sphere. The Baby Magnum has many different forms of interfaces such as a control column, several hundred buttons, eight levers of various sizes, a keyboard, a trackball, special goggles to track the movement of the pilot's eyes, among others. The craft's undercarriage is in a reverse Y-shape. Seven arms extend from the back of the sphere with guns attached to them.

title: artificial_academy_2
body:
([i]Jinkou Gakuen 2[/i])

A sandbox dating sim game made by the Japanese company ILLUSION.

In it, the player creates a 25 character classroom of students, and plays as one throughout a school year. The game is free of any real game "mechanics", minigames, schedules and does not even have an ending (except for the bad ends wherein the character dies or is expelled). The appeal comes from a the cast of characters and from the extensive customization options, which can be furthered by the use of mods.

The game has never been translated into any language and has not been legitimately released outside of Japan, but scripters and modders on hongfire, 4chan and other sites banded together to create an extensive "release" for the game, containing a huge amount of modifications, modding options, custom characters and voices. 

You can buy the base game (in Japanese) from ebay with no difficulty, but it's region locked so you won't be able to play it. 

If you're interested, users on 4chan have done an admirable job making it available, if not easy to obtain. An English-language install is possible, but you will need, among other things, the base game (off a torrent) an emulated CD mounter/burner such as DAEMON tools, the Illusion Wizzard by DarkHound, the dialogue translation, the HGG UI translation, the translated names pack, all the DLC (also from a torrent) applocale for reading the Japanese-language files (if your system is running 8.1 on windows or lower) or a locale emulator (if using windows 10). The game cannot be run on mac. You'll also need the install guide found on the aa2 general http://boards.4chan.org/vg/catalog (ctrl-f "aa2", you'll see it) as the install process is exceptionally complicated.

h4.See also

title: horizontal_bar
body:
A catchall tag for equipment that has a single horizontal bar where a user can lift and suspend themselves for various athletic or gymnastic exercises.

What is covered by this tag:

* [b]Athletic pull-up or chin-up bars[/b], a piece of equipment that is common in outdoor playgrounds and exercise stations.  Constructed of a metal bar suspended by wooden or metal supports on either side.  May be a triple or multi-unit where several are side-by-side and share supports between bars.
** Currently is the only type of equipment actually being depicted by this tag.
* [b]Gymnastics horizontal or high bar[/b], a piece of equipment composed of a steel or metal bar suspended by a rigid structure and cables. It is used by male gymnasts in performing various swings, aerial releases, and dismounts.  Due to users strongly swinging their weight on the bar, cables are necessary to keep the unit firmly restrained.

title: shisha_no_teikoku
body:
The Empire of Corpses (屍者の帝国 Shisha no Teikoku, lit "The Empire of Corpses") is a Japanese novel written by Japanese authors Itou Keikaku and Enjou Tou. The novel was published by Kawade Shobo Shinsha on the August of 2012. It won the Special Award for the 33rd Japan SF Grand Prize (日本SF大賞 Nihon SF Taisho) and the Best Japanese Long Story Award for the 44th Seiun Award (星雲賞 Seiunshou).

Set in an alternate timeline, the world during the late nineteen hundreds is experiencing a rapid change due to the Corpse Revolution, a period of technological advancement where corpses are revived and used as replacement for the living for manual labor and war efforts. John H. Watson is studying as a medical student in the University of London when Professor Van Helsing chooses him to travel to Afghanistan as a spy to investigate the Corpse Empire created by Alexei Karamazov.

h4. Characters

Most of the characters have [[real life]]/19th-century fiction counterparts. Use "_(shisha_no_teikoku)" as a qualifier.

title: bao_sanniang
body:
A folklorical character of the Three Kingdoms era of China, she is [[Guan Suo]]'s first wife, who had to defeat her to wed her.

She was added in [[Shin Sangoku Musou]] [[shin_sangoku_musou_6|at the same time]] as Guan Suo as a flavor character. She was initially infamous for being the least clothed character in the series. [[shin_sangoku_musou_7|The next game]] gave her a similar costume to her husband.

title: guan_suo
body:
The fictional third son of [[Guan Yu]]. He is a Shu officer who fought in the pacification of the Nanman tribes. A popular subject in folklore, he is usually portrayed as a beautiful and handsome young man. His good looks and strength scored him 4 wives, including [[Bao Sanniang]].

This tag is primarly used for his [[Shin Sangoku Musou]] portrayals. True to his nickname of "[[flower|Hua]] Guan Suo", he is portrayed with a flower on his hair.

title: hanjuku_hero
body:
(はんじゅくヒーロー) "Softboiled Hero"

A Japanese-only game series by Square-Enix released originally over the Wii store.  

Playing vaguely like a cross between Paper Mario and Suikoden, gameplay is varied, and involves leading armies of 2d sprites against other armies, but has multiple game modes (including roguelike dungeons fought with armies that battle by smashing into one another as sprites fly away when they die in a charge) and severely oddball humor in between. There are crossovers with classic Final Fantasy games, such as summoning Final Fantasy IV characters from eggs during battle.

The main character is Lord Almamoon, who has to save his kingdom from various dangers each game.  

There are four main games, and a spin-off game for the 3DS, "Egg Monster Hero".

title: legend_of_the_cryptids
body:
From Wiki: http://legendofthecryptids.wikia.com/wiki/Legend_of_the_Cryptids
[quote] 
Legend of the Cryptids is a trading card, massively multiplayer online role-playing fantasy game created and published by developer Applibot. It was released to iOS based devices on May 10, 2012, with a version released for Android based devices on August 15, 2012. A version of the game was released in Japan by the title "Legend of Monsters" on June 9, 2012.

The game is set in the fictional world of Neotellus, a planet orbited by three moons in a distant galaxy. The planet is inhabited by both humans, as well as various creatures known as Cryptids. The game revolves around the on-going conflict between the humans and Cryptids, and a malevolent Cryptid devouring entity known as the Shadow King, who's goal is the destruction of the world of Neotellus and all of its inhabitants.

The gameplay revolves around collecting cards based on the game's Cryptid inhabitants, and using them to participate in various Events and Quests, as well as in battles with other players.
[/quote]

title: teedo
body:
A fictional [[alien]] character from the new sequel trilogy of [[Star Wars]] films.

[b]Teedo[/b] is a short green-skinned humanoid scavenger who operated in the wastes of the desert world of [[jakku_(star_wars)|Jakku]] approximately thirty years after the Battle of Endor. 

Like the rest of his species, which was also known as Teedo, Teedo had a strange sense of identity that led him to refer to himself as Teedo.

Teedo wears a mask, is armed with a [[staff]] and rides a [[Luggabeast]] as a beast of burden.

He first appeared in the [[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]] movie from 2015. Teedo was physically portrayed by veteran stuntman "Kiran Shah":http://starwars.wikia.com/wiki/Kiran_Shah who played an Ewok and the tortured dustbin droid in [[jabba_the_hutt|Jabba]]'s dungeon in Return of the Jedi.

title: luggabeast
body:
A fictional [[alien]] creature from the new sequel trilogy of [[Star Wars]] films. It first appeared in the [[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]] movie from 2015.

The [b]Luggabeast[/b] is a type of non-sentient, quadruped alien species that lived in the galaxy. In the decades following the Battle of Endor, luggabeasts could be found on the desert world of [[jakku_(star_wars)|Jakku]], where the [[Teedo]] population used the beasts for scavenging. 

To help them locate droids and other valuables, the Teedos gave the creatures several cybernetic implants and other [[robot]]ic enhancements such as [[armor]], detection equipment, sensors or optical instruments turning them into [[cyborg]] beasts of burden.

A type of dessert or trifle that can be served hot or cold. It can also be known as an "ice-box cake". Bread, sponge cake or biscuits/cookies are used to line a mold, which is then filled with a fruit puree or custard. It can also be made using layers of breadcrumbs.

Classically, stale bread dipped in butter was used as the lining, but sponge cake or ladyfingers may be used today. The filling may be covered with a thin layer of similarly flavored gelatin.

title: isaf
body:
[i]For "a real-world NATO-led security mission":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Security_Assistance_Force], use [[international_security_assistance_force|its full name]] as the tag.[/i]

The Independent State Allied Forces, the player's faction in the game [[Ace Combat 04]].

I.S.A.F. resembles the United Nations in its operation, formed of representatives from many smaller nations of the Usean continent that pool their resources in times of need.
During the Continental War, its military forces were nearly exterminated by the Erusians. Pushed back to a small island country called North Point, I.S.A.F. forces hunkered down to attempt to endure one final assault. This is where the player (as [[Mobius 1]]) comes in, and the events of the game begin. The military force ceased operations and disbanded after Mobius 1 deployed for Operation Katina; a follow up campaign that took place one year after the end of the The Usean Continental War, eliminating a remnant Eruseain faction called "Free Erusea". Which is found in the [[ace_combat_5]] arcade mode.
